-- Treasury to sell preferred stock in five firms
-- 
-- Tue Aug 21, 2012 10:14am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/08/21/us-usa-treasury-tarp-idUSBRE87K0M220120821

 

 WASHINGTON  (Reuters) - The Treasury said on Tuesday it will sell preferred stock in five banks acquired during the financial crisis. 
 The preferred shares are in BNC Bancorp, First Community Corporation, First National Corporation, Guaranty Federal Bancshares and Mackinac Financial Corporation. Treasury said the auctions would begin on Tuesday at 10 a.m. (Reporting by  Jason Lange ; Editing by  Chizu Nomiyama )